                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="alexandriaquartet_sng_1"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">a series of four novels by <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/lawrence-durrell" title="Lawrence Durrell definition"><span class="ndv">Lawrence Durrell</span></a> about the complicated love affairs of a group of friends in Alexandria, Egypt, in the 1930s. The four books are <span class="ebi">Justine</span> (1957), <span class="ebi">Balthazar</span> (1958), <span class="ebi">Mountolive</span> (1958) and <span class="ebi">Clea</span> (1960). The series forms Durrell's best-known work.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
